### 6. Enable Comments in Your Blog Posts

Finally, to enable comments on a specific blog post, add `enableComments: true` to the front matter of the Markdown file.

For example, in `blog/2025-06-26-welcome-to-portfolio.md`:

```markdown
---
title: "Welcome to my Portfolio"
authors: austenstone
tags: [docusaurus, portfolio, blog]
enableComments: true
---

Your blog post content...
```

Now, your blog posts with `enableComments: true` will have a Giscus comment section at the bottom.

For more detailed information, you can refer to these resources:

*   **Giscus:** [https://giscus.app/](https://giscus.app/)
*   **Docusaurus Swizzling:** [https://docusaurus.io/docs/swizzling](https://docusaurus.io/docs/swizzling)
*   **Tutorial:** [How to add Giscus comments to Docusaurus](https://dev.to/m19v/how-to-add-giscus-comments-to-docusaurus-439h)

